1
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:54,120
Come on!

2
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,760
<i>You've wandered pretty far, haven't you?</i>

3
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,720
I'm asking you.

4
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,760
What are you doing here?

5
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,720
I've got it.

6
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:11,200
When was my daughter’s phone tapped?

7
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,560
Your apology

8
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:15,080
means nothing anymore.

9
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,800
You're dismissed.

10
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,880
<i>I have something for you to do.</i>

11
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,040
Good afternoon,

12
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:21,960
Commander.

13
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:23,480
That man Wayu…

14
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,600
I want to test something about him.

15
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,800
How is it?

16
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,480
Just as beautiful as I imagined.

17
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:32,320
Do you need any help?

18
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:34,040
Let me just touch up my makeup for a bit.

19
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,440
Thank you.

20
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,960
Just this once, Dad.

21
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,520
The DNA results, sir.

22
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,920
Wayu isn't Black Doc.

23
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,040
Fahsai.

24
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,040
Samut.

25
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,200
Why are you sitting here alone?

26
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,960
I was waiting for you.

27
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,800
I just wanted to warn you about Dharn.

28
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:15,120
No matter what, he's still
on the opposite side from Dad

29
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,279
and us.

30
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,360
But we didn't do anything wrong.

31
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:21,240
He's even helping with the foundation.

32
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:23,440
You're still too inexperienced
in politics.

33
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:27,240
You don't see the game, you're being used

34
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,640
to build his image.

35
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:32,840
I think you're overthinking this, Samut.

36
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,120
If the public benefits in the end,

37
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,480
shouldn't you be happy?

38
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,280
I know you're worried.

39
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:46,160
But you and Dad wanted me to run
the foundation on my own, didn't you?

40
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,560
Wait.

41
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,000
It's fine.

42
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,680
Do your job.

43
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:02,840
But if he causes any problems,

44
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,560
you have to tell me.

45
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:09,920
Okay.

46
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:15,640
Wait.

47
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,480
Yes?

48
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,240
Can I ask you one more thing?

49
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,320
Don't go bothering Commander Singha again.

50
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:45,840
Peeraka's case was over a long time ago.

51
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:06,280
Hello?

52
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,680
Yong,

53
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,760
let me ask you something.

54
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:11,920
If everyone in your house
tells you to stop investigating

55
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,640
something you're suspicious about

56
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,320
and insists there's nothing,

57
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:16,960
what would you do?

58
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,920
Then I'd keep investigating.

59
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,960
If there's really nothing,

60
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,040
why?

61
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,320
Why?

62
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,280
Why would they stop you?

63
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,760
<i>Wait.</i>

64
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:32,920
Don't tell me you're still suspicious

65
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,320
about what happened
when you met Commander Singha.

66
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,520
Yeah.

67
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:39,880
Something about him feels off.

68
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:43,880
How am I supposed
to keep digging into this?

69
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,240
Oh.

70
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:50,600
I know. If you can't get answers
from the source,

71
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:53,120
then investigate the people around him.

72
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,760
The people around him?

73
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,760
Someone's bound to slip up.

74
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,440
Ms. Fahsai,

75
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,080
your phone that shut down

76
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:03,480
when you dropped it,

77
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,040
I had it repaired.

78
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,520
Thank you so much. I'll call you later.

79
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,520
ANAWIN PIPATPONG

80
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,400
STUDENT NUMBER

81
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:22,880
PIPATPONG HOTEL

82
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:28,280
ACADEMIC RESULTS

83
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:31,240
MORE SEARCH RESULTS

84
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,840
ANAWIN

85
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:49,440
ANAWIN PI

86
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:58,320
Is this a person's Instagram or a dog's?

87
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:07,760
"Another year
and I still haven't forgotten you."

88
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:12,920
MS. PEEKUL JAIAREE

89
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,520
Jaiaree?

90
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:48,240
Where are you going?
Why didn't you wait for me?

91
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:51,800
I have something to do today.
Just go wait for me at the foundation.

92
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:55,520
What is it? Where?

93
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,320
Let me take you.

94
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,720
Just do as I say.

95
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,320
- Yes.
- Please check this.

96
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,880
Sure.

97
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,880
I'll get it done.

98
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,040
Thank you.

99
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,080
Captain Anawin.

100
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,600
Good morning.

101
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,200
Good morning, Ms. Fahsai.

102
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:22,480
Commander Singha isn't here.

103
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,040
I'm not here for him.

104
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:24,960
I'm here for you.

105
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,000
Can we talk?

106
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:31,800
Sure.

107
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:35,080
It won't take long.

108
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,760
Let's talk at a café.

109
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,520
Wow.

110
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,120
Hey.

111
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,280
I really need to talk about this.

112
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,440
Being Captain Anawin must be nice.

113
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:12,280
Girls keep coming to see him nonstop.

114
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,400
The vet girl the other day,

115
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,520
now the minister's daughter.

116
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,640
Wow.

117
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,560
Why is he so popular?

118
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,680
And now they're going for coffee,
just the two of them.

119
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:23,440
Don't know if they're
just drinking coffee.

120
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:24,600
Well, should we go

121
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:26,120
and see for ourselves?

122
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,640
- Let's go.
- Hey.

123
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:31,320
I'm not assigned to that case.

124
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:33,560
I don't know anything.

125
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:36,000
Sorry for wasting your time.

126
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:39,520
You may not be involved
as the officer in charge,

127
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,680
but you might be connected
to someone in the case.

128
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,840
What do you mean?

129
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:54,760
‪MS. PEEKUL JAIAREE

130
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:18,360
What is Peekul Jaiaree to you?

131
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:24,200
From the hashtag,
she's more than just someone you know.

132
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,960
Peekul was my girlfriend.

133
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:42,800
If you're asking me for the truth,
I can't give it to you.

134
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,480
I was also kept out of the case.

135
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,960
I really don't know anything.

136
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:54,400
Then, do you know Peeraka?

137
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,960
<i>Back then, he was an intern.</i>

138
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:07,360
<i>He was barely home. I didn't see him much.</i>

139
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:11,760
But Kul told me

140
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,480
they fought a lot.

141
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,080
So maybe--

142
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:19,560
Siblings fight, yes,

143
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,440
but that doesn't mean
they kill each other.

144
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:27,560
Do you really believe
he could kill his own sister and mother?

145
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,560
Don't ask me how I feel.

146
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:47,240
The evidence and witnesses
all point to Peeraka.

147
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,400
That's the conclusion.

148
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:19,800
I was once kidnapped.

149
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,200
Peeraka saved me.

150
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:29,600
Otherwise, I wouldn't be here today.

151
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:33,480
He really saved you?

152
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:35,840
Yes.

153
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,360
He risked his life for me.

154
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:42,120
If he was truly that cruel and heartless,

155
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,720
why would he save me?

156
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,920
Think about it.

157
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:50,280
If he didn't do it and was framed,

158
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:53,800
then your girlfriend's family

159
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,840
never got justice.

160
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,720
Who told you to follow me?

161
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,760
It's my job.

162
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,800
By the way,

163
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:19,280
why did you come here?

164
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,240
Personal business.

165
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,840
And I don't have to tell you what it is.

166
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,800
Dad asked you to protect me,

167
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:30,440
not to control me.

168
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:32,120
You don't need to know everything.

169
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:42,960
Give me the keys.

170
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,680
I'll drive.

171
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,640
What about your car?

172
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,120
I'll have my guys pick it up.

173
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:56,960
Didn't you say you wouldn't
make things difficult for me?

174
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:42,440
Wait.

175
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,720
The ground's uneven.

176
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,320
You should change your shoes.

177
00:15:58,280 --> 00:15:59,960
You're surprisingly attentive.

178
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:03,360
But I'm fine.

179
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,080
Let me help.

180
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,640
Hey, I'll do it myself.

181
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:16,520
We're planning to turn this underpass
into a sports area

182
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:19,680
for local kids and teens.

183
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,560
Mr. Dharn proposed it.

184
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:26,160
He said his party will help find sponsors.

185
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,240
Are you okay?

186
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,600
Did you get hurt?

187
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,640
I'm fine.

188
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:05,040
Are you taking special care of me
or something?

189
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:11,400
Does it look like that?

190
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:19,240
Maybe.

191
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,000
Who wants to lose their job?

192
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:28,280
That young captain,

193
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:31,760
maybe you'd prefer him
to protect you instead.

194
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,840
So that's what this is about.

195
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:37,480
Don't worry.

196
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:40,440
I asked him for something else,
not to replace you.

197
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,760
Good to hear.

198
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:50,880
You know, the police
aren't your only option.

199
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:58,080
Sometimes, people like us

200
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:00,240
are more useful.

201
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:07,280
How many times have you gone
to the Special Investigation Unit?

202
00:19:08,280 --> 00:19:09,880
How many officers have you talked to?

203
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:12,840
Any progress?

204
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,280
You don't have to abandon that way…

205
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:24,400
but having more than one option
is better, isn't it?

206
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,760
I can help you.

207
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:40,120
<i>Fahsai, what have you been up to? Tell me.</i>

208
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:44,640
<i>Maybe I should let him</i>
<i>help investigate Peeraka's case.</i>

209
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,080
Mr. Dharn says
he just finished his meeting.

210
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:58,480
He'll be late.

211
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:01,680
Then, let's check over there.

212
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:08,480
<i>No. If he knows,</i>
<i>Samut and Dad might find out too.</i>

213
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:09,840
<i>Don't trust him yet.</i>

214
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:15,560
Where's the key? Give it to me!

215
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:17,920
- No! Stop it. I need it to make a living.
- Hand it over.

216
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,600
- Don't do it.
- Give it to me now.

217
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:21,160
- Hey! Give it to me!
- Stop!

218
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,360
- No!
- Give it to me.

219
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:24,520
- Where is it? Give it to me.
- I won't give it to you.

220
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:27,040
- I need it to make a living.
- Give it to me.

221
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:28,480
Mind your own business!

222
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:29,480
Come this way.

223
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,680
What?

224
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:07,840
Go.

225
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,480
Hey, get him!

226
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:11,080
- You go.
- Me? Okay.

227
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:31,600
You got me beaten up!

228
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,760
Mr. Dharn.

229
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,000
Mr. Dharn.

230
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:03,160
Enough. Don't hurt my son.

231
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:06,200
Are you hurt?

232
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,400
- Are you hurt?
- Call an ambulance.

233
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:10,440
Are you hurt?

234
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:13,680
Hang in there.

235
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:38,880
This camera too, please.

236
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,320
Smile, please.

237
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,640
- Beautiful.
- This way, please.

238
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:45,120
Nice.

239
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:46,720
Thank you.

240
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:52,720
Thank you for saving Fahsai.

241
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,560
Thank you so much.

242
00:22:57,240 --> 00:23:00,440
We really owe you one.

243
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:03,520
I don't know how to repay
your courage and sacrifice.

244
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:06,400
Please consider us indebted to you.

245
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:10,600
Please don't say that.

246
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:13,240
Ms. Fahsai has been very kind to me.

247
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:16,400
I could never let her be in danger.

248
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:22,480
To make sure neither my sister nor you

249
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:26,080
ever have to face
something dangerous like this again,

250
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:28,880
I think your party should coordinate

251
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,400
with other foundations as well.

252
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:39,000
Mahasamut means well.

253
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:43,600
I think we shouldn't be talking
about work right now.

254
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:47,200
We just want to send our support
and wish you a speedy recovery,

255
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:50,000
so you can get back
to serving the country soon.

256
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:53,560
Alright, we should get going,

257
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,600
so you can rest.

258
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,480
You're leaving already, Minister?

259
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,960
Ms. Fahsai,
have you seen the trend on Twitter?

260
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,840
It's number one right now.

261
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,080
A trend?

262
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,080
What trend?

263
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:12,760
<i>I love him. Why is he so brave?</i>

264
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:15,040
<i>She's the daughter of a politician</i>
<i>from the opposite side.</i>

265
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:16,760
<i>He's the hope of this country.</i>

266
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:19,000
<i>I thought I was watching a K-drama.</i>

267
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:20,960
<i>The man is handsome,</i>
<i>the woman is beautiful.</i>

268
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:23,640
<i>I never thought watching the news</i>
<i>could make me scream</i>

269
00:24:23,720 --> 00:24:25,720
<i>into my pillow harder</i>
<i>than watching a drama.</i>

270
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:28,680
<i>Am I the only one</i>
<i>secretly shipping these two?</i>

271
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,200
<i>He literally saved her life.</i>

272
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,520
SAM

273
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:35,480
Yes?

274
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:38,120
Bro, you saw it, right?

275
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:42,760
You're the one
who saved Ms. Fahsai,

276
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:44,720
but nobody's talking about you at all.

277
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:45,720
Look at Dharn.

278
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:46,800
Everyone's obsessing over him.

279
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:48,720
This is totally unfair.

280
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:50,400
So what do we do?

281
00:24:57,960 --> 00:24:59,160
Nothing.

282
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:02,840
What? Then Dharn gets
all the glory for himself.

283
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:04,240
And what do you get out of it?

284
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,000
Even if I don't get the glory,

285
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,400
at least

286
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:12,720
someone else is losing face.

287
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:18,160
Come sit with me over there.

288
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:20,360
Don't visit Dharn again.

289
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:23,760
This is an order.

290
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:26,480
If I don't allow it,

291
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,640
don't even think about it.

292
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,040
Samut,

293
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:32,960
Mr. Dharn got hurt because of me.

294
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:35,640
If he got hurt,
that's his own fault for being careless.

295
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:40,240
And the reason you got dragged
into danger in the first place

296
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:42,200
was because of his work.

297
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:44,320
You can't blame Mr. Dharn.

298
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:46,720
I agreed to do that work myself.

299
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:49,320
And now you're defending him?

300
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,880
Twitter is making enough
of a spectacle out of this.

301
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:56,120
If you don't care about your own image,

302
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:58,680
then at least care about mine and Dad's.

303
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,040
What exactly did I do wrong?

304
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:04,240
People made those connections themselves.
Why react to it?

305
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:05,560
You're being unreasonable.

306
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,280
Fahsai.

307
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:09,360
Hey, hey, enough, enough.

308
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:11,200
Hey.

309
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:14,040
Fahsai,

310
00:26:14,120 --> 00:26:16,160
your brother is only warning you
because he cares.

311
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:17,480
Alright?

312
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:19,960
Maybe he was too harsh,
but he really is worried about you.

313
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,160
Fahsai.

314
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:36,920
And you, you went too far.

315
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:42,720
Learn to control yourself.
Don't let your emotions control you.

316
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:56,800
You're the one

317
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:59,640
who should've been stabbed

318
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:02,560
instead of that sly fox.

319
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:16,160
He's angry right now.

320
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,840
Please don't take it personally.

321
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:24,360
Thank you.

322
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:55,040
Have you calmed down yet?

323
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:03,640
When Fahsai cools down,

324
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,280
she'll understand

325
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:07,120
that you only did all that

326
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,880
because you care about her.

327
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,360
The truth is, that wasn't even enough.

328
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:17,880
Fahsai should be more careful
around Dharn.

329
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:22,520
She shouldn't let him
get close to her so easily.

330
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:25,520
Well,

331
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:28,480
I envy your sister.

332
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:35,600
What are you saying?

333
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:39,280
I'm your girlfriend,

334
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,800
and yet you've never been jealous

335
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:46,040
or worried like this
when I'm around other men.

336
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:47,360
Isn't that something to envy?

337
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:25,880
Women who talk back and get away with it

338
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:28,880
only exist in dramas.

339
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:36,280
If you don't know what to say,

340
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:39,960
then stay quiet.

341
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:47,040
Someone who loves herself

342
00:29:48,880 --> 00:29:49,920
as much as you do

343
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:55,960
doesn't know how to love
or care about anyone else.

344
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:03,400
So don't you dare judge me.

345
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:07,400
And don't you dare
cross the line with my sister again.

346
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,480
How did you get in here?

347
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:35,640
How I got in here

348
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,120
is none of your business.

349
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,440
What is your business is this.

350
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:46,200
Stay away from Fahsai.

351
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:50,080
But we work together.

352
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:52,360
Then stop working with her.

353
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,000
Hm?

354
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:58,400
I'm warning you nicely.

355
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:06,440
Stay away from my sister.

356
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:55,240
Open this for me.

357
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:03,840
How many times have I told you
not to do that?

358
00:33:11,440 --> 00:33:12,680
Are you here to box?

359
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:16,960
You want me to be your sparring partner?

360
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:26,880
What a giant third wheel.

361
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:30,760
That's fine. I can go do something else.

362
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:32,600
Good.

363
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:34,120
Then I won't have to break a sweat.

364
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:35,600
No, don't.

365
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:38,280
Hey.

366
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,400
If you're done here, just go.

367
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,080
Just let her be.

368
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,880
Mahasamut is that possessive
of his sister?

369
00:34:12,560 --> 00:34:13,600
More than his girlfriend.

370
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:16,800
Wow, I'm jealous.

371
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:19,600
I wish I had a big brother
who was that possessive too.

372
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:22,320
What do I have to do?

373
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,560
I'd like to be possessive of you too.

374
00:34:41,639 --> 00:34:42,679
But…

375
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:48,440
even now, no guys are going after you.

376
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:52,000
Don't want you ending up single
your whole life.

377
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:56,600
Hey, Wayu!

378
00:34:57,320 --> 00:35:01,040
Exercise more. Then more guys
will come after you.

379
00:35:01,680 --> 00:35:02,920
Whoa.

380
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,800
Hey.

381
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,120
Wayu!

382
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:11,160
Good. There, plus two more.

383
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:12,360
That's enough!

384
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:16,680
Mr. Wayu.

385
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,760
What are you going to do about Mahasamut?

386
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:27,480
MAHASAMUT

387
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:34,360
Hello, Mr. Samut.

388
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:36,160
Take good care of Fahsai.

389
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:39,080
Don't let her visit
or meet with Dharn again.

390
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:46,320
Understood.

391
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,200
Good.

392
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:54,360
What did he say?

393
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:59,120
He wants me to keep
a close watch on his sister.

394
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:03,640
And?

395
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,280
Well…

396
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:09,000
then I'll arrange it better
than he ever expected.

397
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,080
Hello, Mr. Marut.

398
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:43,880
Oh, you're here already?

399
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:46,080
I'll send someone to get you.

400
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:48,720
Yes.

401
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:50,920
Okay.

402
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:58,760
Please go pick up Mr. Marut,
the social worker.

403
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,800
He doesn't have a car.

404
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:02,760
I'll share the location.

405
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,000
Is something wrong?

406
00:37:15,880 --> 00:37:16,800
No.

407
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:09,880
TAXI METER

408
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:16,920
Please go quickly.

409
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:23,680
Please get out of the car.

410
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:35,200
If I drive after you,

411
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:39,000
I'll probably get to the hospital
before you do.

412
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:54,680
Here's your compensation.

413
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:02,640
You lied to me first.

414
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:05,040
Didn't you say you wouldn't
make things difficult for me?

415
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,640
I did send you to pick someone up.

416
00:39:08,240 --> 00:39:10,360
At least if Samut scolds you,
you'd have an excuse.

417
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,320
You think your brother would listen to me?

418
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:16,160
What kind of bodyguard

419
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:19,240
gets fooled by an excuse that shallow?

420
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:22,920
Don't you think this is too much?

421
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:26,160
I just want to go visit a friend.

422
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:29,720
Why do politics and those headlines
have to matter more?

423
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:32,560
Compared to what Mr. Dharn did for me,

424
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:35,440
all that other stuff
doesn't matter at all.

425
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:13,080
I'd like some privacy, please.

426
00:40:17,520 --> 00:40:19,200
Just sitting here working alone

427
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:20,920
shouldn't be a problem, right?

428
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,800
Want to go get some coffee?

429
00:40:58,520 --> 00:41:00,480
Fahsai went out with Wayu?

430
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:04,840
Don't let her out of your sight.

431
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:10,680
And make sure Wayu doesn't take her
to see Dharn.

432
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:14,280
Good.

433
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:45,160
If your brother asks where you are,

434
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:47,360
say you're here working.

435
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:51,600
You've got a meeting
around here this afternoon anyway.

436
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:54,520
You think my brother
would really check that closely?

437
00:42:22,920 --> 00:42:24,080
Yes, Samut.

438
00:42:24,160 --> 00:42:25,240
Fahsai,

439
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:28,800
my work might finish early today,
so I'm calling to let you know.

440
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:32,720
Maybe I'll come pick you up
from the foundation this evening.

441
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:45,000
Right now,

442
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:48,720
I'm out working at a coffee shop.

443
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:52,920
It's just…

444
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:54,920
I mean…

445
00:42:55,520 --> 00:43:00,400
Well, I have a meeting around here,

446
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:03,760
so I probably
won't be going back to the foundation.

447
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:05,960
Okay, that's fine.

448
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:08,680
I'll call again later then.

449
00:43:09,920 --> 00:43:10,800
Okay.

450
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:20,400
Here.

451
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:24,040
Don't be stunned for too long.

452
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:24,960
There's not much time.

453
00:43:31,080 --> 00:43:32,560
I'll go order coffee.

454
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:34,480
You go change your clothes.

455
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:17,640
Hey! Isn't this a bit much?

456
00:45:18,280 --> 00:45:21,800
We're a couple, remember?
Just checking in at a café together.

457
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:25,240
A couple? We can just be friends.

458
00:45:25,840 --> 00:45:28,760
Friends? You and me, as friends?

459
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:31,640
I don't think that'll sell.

460
00:45:33,640 --> 00:45:35,040
Hey, let go.

461
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:37,160
Hey.

462
00:45:37,720 --> 00:45:38,960
Let go.

463
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:43,720
Your brother's guy is following you.

464
00:45:44,360 --> 00:45:45,200
Huh?

465
00:45:47,960 --> 00:45:49,320
Don't turn around.

466
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:57,040
Get in the car.

467
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:53,560
Did Samut really send people to follow me?

468
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:55,760
Relax.

469
00:46:57,160 --> 00:46:58,000
Don't panic.

470
00:47:06,080 --> 00:47:08,840
He actually had people tail me?

471
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:12,560
Can't you drive faster?

472
00:47:12,640 --> 00:47:14,360
Is this really as fast as you can go?

473
00:47:14,880 --> 00:47:17,640
If I make a run for it,
we'll definitely get caught.

474
00:47:18,280 --> 00:47:20,880
What if they get close enough to see us?

475
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:23,880
Then keep your head down.
Pretend you're busy on your phone.

476
00:48:04,240 --> 00:48:05,120
What's up?

477
00:48:05,720 --> 00:48:07,080
<i>Where'd you go?</i>

478
00:48:07,160 --> 00:48:08,840
<i>Aren't you supposed</i>
<i>to be watching Ms. Fahsai?</i>

479
00:48:09,520 --> 00:48:10,800
They're still in the room?

480
00:48:10,880 --> 00:48:13,960
Yeah, they're both still in the room.

481
00:48:32,080 --> 00:48:33,520
You should get some rest.

482
00:48:34,280 --> 00:48:36,240
I've already lost enough time
and work as it is.

483
00:48:39,960 --> 00:48:41,160
Excuse me.

484
00:48:45,040 --> 00:48:47,560
Mr. Dharn, someone would like to see you.

485
00:48:48,320 --> 00:48:49,920
I don't want to see anyone right now.

486
00:48:50,560 --> 00:48:51,760
Tell them I need to rest.

487
00:48:51,840 --> 00:48:55,240
Yes, sir. But they asked me
to give you this note.

488
00:49:21,800 --> 00:49:23,120
Are you sure this is okay, sir?

489
00:49:24,960 --> 00:49:26,560
She's just Ms. Fahsai's assistant.

490
00:49:26,640 --> 00:49:28,360
It should be fine. You can go.

491
00:49:29,400 --> 00:49:30,400
Yes, sir.

492
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:47,760
My boss asked me to give this to you.

493
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:52,240
- Miss--
- Just talk normally.

494
00:49:55,920 --> 00:49:56,960
Yes.

495
00:50:01,960 --> 00:50:03,520
Please thank Ms. Fahsai for me.

496
00:50:04,640 --> 00:50:05,840
Of course.

497
00:50:05,920 --> 00:50:08,480
I hope you understand

498
00:50:08,560 --> 00:50:10,480
why she couldn't come here herself.

499
00:50:10,560 --> 00:50:11,960
I understand.

500
00:50:12,840 --> 00:50:15,560
I really appreciate
her kindness and thoughtfulness.

501
00:50:17,760 --> 00:50:19,360
I'll tell her that,

502
00:50:20,240 --> 00:50:22,720
but I don't think
she'd see it as anything courageous.

503
00:50:22,800 --> 00:50:27,360
It's only a small thing
compared to what you did for her.

504
00:50:30,480 --> 00:50:32,280
Anyone would have done the same.

505
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:35,000
But today,

506
00:50:35,680 --> 00:50:38,440
it only makes me more certain
that I chose the right person to protect.

507
00:51:13,440 --> 00:51:14,680
The restroom is that way.

508
00:51:18,600 --> 00:51:20,160
Hurry up.

509
00:51:20,240 --> 00:51:21,560
Traffic is bad at this hour.

510
00:51:35,640 --> 00:51:37,760
You told me not to go near your sister,

511
00:51:38,440 --> 00:51:40,520
but now your sister came to me on her own?

512
00:51:56,760 --> 00:51:58,720
How many more outfits
do I have to change into?

513
00:51:58,800 --> 00:52:00,160
Are you messing with me?

514
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:10,160
It's not just your brother's men.

515
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:13,240
There are also reporters
waiting at the hospital for a story.

516
00:52:13,320 --> 00:52:15,080
Their eyes are sharper than you'd think.

517
00:52:16,240 --> 00:52:17,760
And there are Mr. Dharn's people too.

518
00:52:26,640 --> 00:52:27,600
Hey.

519
00:52:28,720 --> 00:52:30,360
The traffic is so bad.

520
00:52:33,160 --> 00:52:35,720
At this rate, will we even
get there within an hour?

521
00:52:48,960 --> 00:52:50,200
Hey.

522
00:52:50,280 --> 00:52:53,080
We've been gone this long,
won't my brother get suspicious?

523
00:53:41,360 --> 00:53:42,200
Hey, hey, hey.

524
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:44,440
Falling asleep again.

525
00:53:44,520 --> 00:53:45,880
I told you to keep watch the whole time.

526
00:53:46,600 --> 00:53:48,240
You went to the bathroom too.

527
00:53:48,320 --> 00:53:49,240
Yeah, yeah.

528
00:53:59,480 --> 00:54:01,040
They're still at the café?

529
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:02,480
Yes, sir.

530
00:54:04,560 --> 00:54:06,240
It's been three hours already.

531
00:54:06,320 --> 00:54:07,800
Hasn't anyone come out yet?

532
00:54:08,880 --> 00:54:10,160
Then go in and check.

533
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:12,960
Yes, sir. Got it.

534
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:18,720
Hey!

535
00:54:18,800 --> 00:54:20,720
- Sorry.
- Watch where you're going.

536
00:54:22,920 --> 00:54:24,160
Wait.

537
00:54:25,840 --> 00:54:26,840
Is something wrong?

538
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,680
Sorry, my mistake.

539
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:37,600
What's the matter?

540
00:54:38,200 --> 00:54:40,240
Sorry, wrong room.

541
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:10,360
Hey, I'll be right back.

542
00:55:51,520 --> 00:55:53,200
What are you looking at?

543
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:56,960
Nothing. Just transferring money
into a man's account.

544
00:55:57,040 --> 00:55:58,560
A man's?

545
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:01,280
Who is he?

546
00:56:03,720 --> 00:56:06,160
MRS. KULVIPA JAIAREE FOR PEERAKA JAIAREE

547
00:56:09,360 --> 00:56:11,320
You're so gullible.

548
00:56:12,120 --> 00:56:13,920
It's my little brother's account.

549
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:14,880
I get it now.

550
00:56:16,320 --> 00:56:18,440
How is Peeraka so lucky?

551
00:56:18,520 --> 00:56:20,840
He has a kind angel for an older sister.

552
00:56:20,920 --> 00:56:23,360
You work so hard,
yet instead of saving money for yourself,

553
00:56:23,440 --> 00:56:24,800
you save it all for your brother.

554
00:56:26,880 --> 00:56:28,160
He's lucky.

555
00:56:28,240 --> 00:56:30,160
He just doesn't know it.

556
00:56:30,240 --> 00:56:32,440
These days, he thinks I'm some evil witch.

557
00:56:32,520 --> 00:56:34,880
He thinks I'm stealing the money

558
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:37,240
he wants to spend on his girlfriend
and using it myself.

559
00:56:44,120 --> 00:56:45,120
Kul,

560
00:56:45,200 --> 00:56:48,360
then why don't you
just tell him straight out

561
00:56:48,440 --> 00:56:50,960
that you mean well?

562
00:56:53,480 --> 00:56:54,760
If I told him,

563
00:56:54,840 --> 00:56:57,360
he'd just say he can manage his own money.

564
00:56:57,440 --> 00:57:00,840
But every single time,
it ends up all gone on some woman.

565
00:57:03,240 --> 00:57:05,920
That's why I have to play the villain.

566
00:57:06,680 --> 00:57:08,360
Someone like Raka,

567
00:57:08,440 --> 00:57:09,800
when he loves someone,

568
00:57:09,880 --> 00:57:11,520
he gives everything.

569
00:57:13,000 --> 00:57:14,600
But no matter how much
he loves his girlfriend,

570
00:57:15,240 --> 00:57:17,920
he loves Mom and me more.

571
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:19,080
I know it.

572
00:57:23,240 --> 00:57:24,200
And you know what?

573
00:57:26,080 --> 00:57:28,040
There's one more person
who loves you the most?

574
00:57:29,480 --> 00:57:30,480
Who?

575
00:57:32,080 --> 00:57:32,920
It's me.

576
00:57:34,520 --> 00:57:36,960
I know.

577
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,720
- You really know?
- Yeah.

578
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:42,640
If you know, then give me a reward.
Right here.

579
00:57:42,720 --> 00:57:45,000
A reward here?

580
00:57:45,640 --> 00:57:47,560
Okay.

581
00:57:48,840 --> 00:57:50,120
You're evil.

582
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:52,280
- No, not like that.
- Then what do you want?

583
00:57:52,960 --> 00:57:55,160
Alright.

584
00:58:24,680 --> 00:58:26,160
Hello, Captain.

585
00:58:26,240 --> 00:58:28,040
Have you thought about it?

586
00:58:28,120 --> 00:58:31,320
I'm going to try to uncover the truth
behind the Jaiaree family case.

587
00:58:32,600 --> 00:58:33,840
Really?

588
00:58:33,920 --> 00:58:35,400
Thank you so much.

589
00:58:35,480 --> 00:58:37,080
No need to thank me.

590
00:58:38,280 --> 00:58:40,120
If Peeraka didn't do it,

591
00:58:40,720 --> 00:58:43,320
<i>then I want to know who did.</i>

592
00:58:44,400 --> 00:58:46,640
And I'll make sure they pay for it.

593
00:58:52,440 --> 00:58:53,480
Who were you talking to?

594
00:58:55,640 --> 00:58:57,320
You look awfully pleased.

595
00:58:58,040 --> 00:58:59,920
Just work stuff.

596
00:59:00,480 --> 00:59:02,560
Do I have to report everything to you too?

597
00:59:03,440 --> 00:59:04,520
Hey.

598
00:59:05,280 --> 00:59:06,440
You're still mad at me?

599
00:59:07,960 --> 00:59:10,360
You know I'm only worried about you.

600
00:59:11,520 --> 00:59:15,160
With the way the story came out,
you're a woman,

601
00:59:17,720 --> 00:59:20,600
of course, I have to do everything I can
to protect your dignity.

602
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:29,440
Are you still mad at me?

603
00:59:30,640 --> 00:59:32,960
Is that why you didn't want me
to pick you up at the café?

604
00:59:34,040 --> 00:59:36,200
I told you I was tired.

605
00:59:36,280 --> 00:59:38,640
I already texted you.

606
00:59:39,600 --> 00:59:40,600
Alright then.

607
00:59:41,800 --> 00:59:43,320
Let's have dinner together tonight.

608
00:59:44,120 --> 00:59:47,200
I already told the cook
to make your favorite.

609
00:59:48,440 --> 00:59:49,600
Let's go.

610
00:59:52,320 --> 00:59:53,360
No.

611
00:59:53,960 --> 00:59:55,160
I'm not hungry.

612
00:59:56,880 --> 00:59:57,800
Fahsai.

613
00:59:58,440 --> 00:59:59,480
I'm going to rest.

614
01:00:02,920 --> 01:00:04,360
Oh, Fahsai.

615
01:00:06,240 --> 01:00:07,320
You're back, dear?

616
01:00:10,000 --> 01:00:11,760
I'm going to rest now, Dad.

617
01:00:12,760 --> 01:00:13,960
Fahsai.

618
01:00:18,680 --> 01:00:21,080
Looks like she's still angry with you.

619
01:00:22,840 --> 01:00:24,800
Don't push her so hard.

620
01:00:25,400 --> 01:00:29,080
Dad, being a little upset is normal.

621
01:00:29,720 --> 01:00:31,120
She'll get over it.

622
01:00:32,840 --> 01:00:34,480
- Dad.
- Hm?

623
01:00:35,240 --> 01:00:38,560
But what matters is that
we deal with Dharn first.

624
01:00:39,200 --> 01:00:44,040
That stupid story about Fahsai and Dharn
has to end once and for all.

625
01:00:51,040 --> 01:00:53,560
Are you going back to investigate
the Jaiaree family case?

626
01:00:53,640 --> 01:00:55,680
I'd like to ask for more information.

627
01:00:55,760 --> 01:00:59,280
Think carefully. Are you sure
you didn't hear anything at all?

628
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:01,120
Or did you hear something?

629
01:01:01,200 --> 01:01:04,160
Fahsai, come on, please help me.

630
01:01:10,720 --> 01:01:11,840
Be careful…

631
01:01:15,880 --> 01:01:16,800
A bouquet and a card.

632
01:01:18,760 --> 01:01:19,680
Who sent this?

633
01:01:22,960 --> 01:01:23,920
Mr. Wayu?

634
01:01:25,680 --> 01:01:26,800
Oh.

635
01:01:26,880 --> 01:01:29,920
Mr. Wayu, are you going
to be Mr. Dharn's rival now?

636
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:31,280
<i>I'm here.</i>

637
01:01:31,840 --> 01:01:32,960
<i>Right here.</i>

638
01:01:33,520 --> 01:01:34,440
<i>With you.</i>

639
01:02:39,440 --> 01:02:41,040
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
